Glassworm burrower queen extermination
-1 3 1 1 62 75 3340 5000 5 2000000 0
5769
The glassworm burrower queen has been expanding her tunnel network through the Glasswind Belt at a rate that is destabilizing the ancient glass formations and sealing off the Glasswalk Guide routes that Kiess-certified caravans depend on for safe Reach transit. Individual worm encounters are manageable, but the queen's tunneling will render large sections of the Belt impassable within a season. The Kiess postmaster requires her elimination before the route network can be restored.
The glassworm burrower queen has been destroyed and the network expansion has halted. Glasswalk Guide survey teams have confirmed that the most critical Reach transit corridors are stable and passable with standard precautions. The Kiess postmaster has issued updated route advisories and dispatched scouts to map the extent of the existing tunnel damage for seasonal remediation planning.

